SummaryOfEvents:
The 15 June, after an explosion, a fire of 2 containers loaded with lithium batteries broke out in a hold. The Port Authority decided to shift the vessel to a non commercial adjacent berth ;

- 1st action : the Port Authority and a firefighting team made a tentative with seawater hoses, without conclusive result ;

- 2nd action : CO2 was triggered in 3 times. Soon after, a watch of the temperature was kept with thermal camera ;

- 3rd action :The foam was triggered. The end of the violent fire was then detected and it was decided to let the containers consume ;

- The 18 June, after a continuous watch of the temperature, it was decided to restart the ventilation, first by opening the flaps, then by starting the fans ;

- The 19 June, it was decided to investigate the hold with cameras and gas detectors ;

- The firefighting teams (Port authority and crew) agreed to declare that the fire was out ;

- The vessel was re-shifted to the commercial berth ;

- The hold was open and the salvage plan was enforced.
